We arrive at a price target of \(\) 175\(based upon 2026E EBITDA of\) \sim \(1.6bn and an estimated EV/2026 EBITDA multiple of\) \sim 13.5x\$ . We arrive at our \(\sim 13.5x\) multiple using blended multiple approach on the sum of the parts.

Greater than expected demand for air traffic- Engine leasing utilization reaches/surpasses pre- Covid highs- Adoption of new PMA parts ramps faster than expected- Incremental partnerships like the 2025 Partnership
PMA parts do not receive FAA approval- Engine leasing utilization remains below historical levels- Unable to raise additional partnerships like the 2025 Partnership
5.5x EV/S and 0.18x EV/S/G, which is at a discount to the median of Omada's most relevant HCIT comps (TEM, HIMS, WAY, HNGE, and PHR) at 6.1x. Alternatively, our PT reflects a 8.3x EV/GP.
Upside to margins from technology and multi- condition sales- Higher than expected engagement through new programs/marketing initiatives- GLP- 1 Care Track and new sales channel partnerships
Sales channel concentration leading to risk of client loss- The potential for competition to intensify- Lower than expected member engagement

PT reflects 18.2x EV/EBITDA on '26E Base Case, \(+50\%\) vs LT median (of 12.1x) but \(\sim\) in line with peer premium (Sp. Chems current: 14.3x, \(+50\%\) vs LT med. 9.6x) or a conservative \(\sim 20x\) P/E (on adj. EPS), \(\sim 25\%\) below PRM's \(\sim 26x\) LT median and below peers (Sp. Chems current: \(\sim 23x\) \(+35\%\) vs. LT median \(\sim 17x\) ). PT implies \(3.1\%\) FCF yield (vs peers \(4.0\%\) ). Key risks: market share loss, pricing pressure, execution issues, & idiosyncratic wild season severity risk.
- Severe US wildfire season- Greater Fire Safety pricing/margin improvement vs. expectations- Specialty Product growth above base case (of \~flat)- Accretive/well-received M&A- Upside TSR surprise

- Below 'normal' US wildfire season- Fire Safety pricing/margin degradation- New entrants / competition risk- Specialty Product declines below base case (of \~flat)- Dilutive/not well-received M&A- Downside TSR surprise
